   "source": [
    "# Extended Torus Model\n",
    "\n",
    "In this tutorial, we apply the `circle_bundles` pipeline to confirm a 3-manifold model proposed in [] for high-contrast optical flow patches sampled from the Sintel dataset []. The model is homotopy equivalent to a torus, but the topology cannot be satsfactorally detected from a direct persistence computation. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "b92ca543",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from ripser import ripser\n",
    "from persim import plot_diagrams\n",
    "\n",
    "import circle_bundles as cb"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f343619b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, get a large sample of optical patches from the Sintel dataset:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "89d6386d",

    "import pickle \n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "patches_per_frame = 400\n",
    "folder_path = \".../MPI-Sintel-complete/training/flow\"   #path to Sintel flow frames\n",
    "\n",
    "patch_df, file_paths = cb.get_patch_sample(\n",
    "    folder_path,\n",
    "    patches_per_frame = patches_per_frame,\n",
    "    d = 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('')\n",
    "print(f'{len(patch_df)} optical flow patches sampled')\n",
    "\n",
    "#Downsample if necessary\n",
    "max_samples = 400000\n",
    "if len(patch_df) > max_samples:\n",
    "    patch_df = patch_df.sample(n=max_samples)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3ab67bfc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, preprocess the data -- compute contrast norms and keep only patches with contrast norm in the top 20%.  Then, use a KNN density estimator to measure the density of dataset near each datapoint:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "7aa3076f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "hc_frac = 0.2\n",
    "max_samples = 50000\n",
    "k = [300]\n",
    "\n",
    "patch_df = cb.preprocess_flow_patches(\n",
    "    patch_df,\n",
    "    hc_frac = hc_frac,\n",
    "    max_samples = max_samples,\n",
    "    k_list = k)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6d803342",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, keep only the top 50% of patches by density value:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "ddde57ed",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "p = 0.5 \n",
    "n_samples = int(p*len(patch_df))\n",
    "data = np.vstack(patch_df['patch'])[:n_samples]    #Data is already sorted in decreasing order by density\n",
    "print(f'Downsampled to {len(data)} patches')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cf707d7c",

   "source": [
    "Compute a persistence diagram from a sample of the dataset.  If the dataset is truly concentrated around the proposed torus model, we would expect to see two 1-dimensional persistent classes and a persistent class in dimension 2: "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    "Observe that we see a single 1-dimensional persistent class and no persistent classes in dimension 2.  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "237053ec",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Proceed with local-to-global analysis.  Compute the predominant flow axis in $\\mathbb{RP}^{1}$ (as introduced by Adams et al.) and directionality (as introduced in ---) for each patch, and construct a cover of $\\mathbb{RP}^{1}$.  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "30000702",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/markdown": [
       "### Cover And Nerve Summary\n",
       "- $n_\\text{sets} = 16$, $n_\\text{samples} = 25000$\n",
       "\n",
       "**Recorded Simplex Counts:**\n",
       "\n",
       "- $\\#(\\text{0-simplices}) = 16$\n",
       "- $\\#(\\text{1-simplices}) = 16$\n",
       "- *No recorded simplices in dimensions* $\\ge 2$"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Markdown object>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 2400x900 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "predom_dirs, ratios = cb.get_predominant_dirs(data)  \n",
    "\n",
    "#Construct a cover of the base space\n",
    "n_landmarks = 16\n",
    "landmarks = np.linspace(0, np.pi, n_landmarks, endpoint= False)\n",
    "overlap = 1.99\n",
    "radius = overlap* np.pi/(2*n_landmarks)\n",
    "\n",
    "cover = cb.MetricBallCover(predom_dirs, landmarks, radius, metric = cb.RP1AngleMetric())\n",
    "cover_data = cover.build()\n",
    "\n",
    "#Show a summary of the construction\n",
    "summ = cover.summarize(plot = True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ee9cadc6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   ]
  },

   "id": "7b7834e8",

     "data": {

    "    data,\n",
    "    cover.U,\n",
    "    p_values=None,\n",
    "    to_view = [0,3,8], #Choose a few diagrams to compute \n",
    "                       #(or compute all by setting to None)\n",
    "    maxdim=1,\n",
    "    n_perm=500,\n",
    "    random_state=None,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = cb.plot_local_rips(\n",
    "    fiber_ids,\n",
    "    rips_list,\n",
    "    n_cols=3,\n",
    "    titles='default',\n",
    "    font_size=20,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "aca09400",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Observe that each $\\pi^{-1}(U_{j})$ has a single 1-dimensional (circular) persistent feature, supporting the hypothesis that the data has the structure of a discrete approximate circle bundle over $\\mathbb{RP}^{1}$. Up to isormorphism, there are two possible global structures for a circle bundle over $\\mathbb{RP}^{1}\\cong\\mathbb{S}^{1}$, namely the torus (trivial) and the Klein bottle (non-orientable). These two possibilities are distinguished by the orientation class $w_{1}$.\n",
    "\n",
    "Now, construct local circular coordinates, compute approximate transition matrices and characteristic classes:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "af1c1b27",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/latex": [
       "$\\displaystyle \\begin{aligned}\\textbf{Diagnostics} & \\\\[6pt]\\quad \\text{Trivialization error} &:\\quad \\varepsilon_{\\text{triv}} := \\sup_{(j\\,k)\\in\\mathcal{N}(\\mathcal{U})}\\sup_{x\\in\\pi^{-1}(U_j\\cap U_k)} d_{\\mathbb{C}}(\\Omega_{jk}f_k(x),f_j(x)) = 0.246\\ \\left(\\varepsilon_{\\text{triv}}^{\\text{geo}}=0.079\\pi\\right)\\\\[3pt]\\quad \\text{Mean triv error} &:\\quad \\bar{\\varepsilon}_{\\text{triv}} = 0.050\\ \\left(\\bar{\\varepsilon}_{\\text{triv}}^{\\text{geo}}=0.016\\pi\\right)\\\\[3pt]\\quad \\text{Surjectivity defect} &:\\quad \\delta := \\sup_{(i\\,j\\,k)\\in\\mathcal{N}(\\mathcal{U})}\\min_{v\\in\\{i,j,k\\}} d_H\\!\\left(f_v(\\pi^{-1}(U_i\\cap U_j\\cap U_k)),\\mathbb{S}^1\\right) = 0.000\\\\[3pt]\\quad \\text{Stability ratio} &:\\quad \\alpha := \\varepsilon_{\\text{triv}}/(1-\\delta) = 0.246\\\\[3pt]\\quad \\text{Cocycle error} &:\\quad \\varepsilon_{\\mathrm{coc}} := \\sup_{(i\\,j\\,k)\\in\\mathcal{N}(\\mathcal{U})}\\left\\|\\Omega_{ij}\\Omega_{jk}\\Omega_{ki}-I\\right\\|_F = 0.000\\\\[3pt]\\quad \\text{Euler rounding dist.} &:\\quad d_\\infty(\\delta_\\omega\\theta,\\tilde{e}) = 0.000\\\\[14pt]\\textbf{Characteristic Classes} & \\\\[6pt]\\quad \\text{Stiefel--Whitney} &:\\quad w_1 = 0\\ (\\text{orientable})\\\\[3pt]\\quad \\text{Euler class} &:\\quad e = 0\\ \\text{(no 2-simplices)}\\end{aligned}$"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Math object>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "bundle = cb.build_bundle(\n",
    "    data,\n",
    "    cover,\n",
    "    show=True,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a0eded27",
   "metadata": {},

    "Since the global structure is trivial, synchronize local circular coordinates to construct a toroidal coordinate system for the dataset: "
